# Example: plan.md

> Copy this file to your project root as `plan.md` before starting any significant task.

---

## Goal
Refactor the authentication module to use JWT instead of session-based auth.

## Inputs
- `src/auth/session.ts` — current session-based implementation
- `src/middleware/auth.ts` — middleware that needs updating
- `docs/api-spec.md` — API contract that must not break

## Done When
- [ ] All existing tests pass (exit code 0)
- [ ] New JWT tests added and passing
- [ ] No `console.log` left in production code
- [ ] `handoff.md` updated with migration notes
- [ ] API contract in `docs/api-spec.md` unchanged

## Steps
1. Read `src/auth/session.ts` and understand current flow
2. Write failing tests for JWT implementation
3. Implement JWT token generation and validation
4. Update `src/middleware/auth.ts` to verify JWT
5. Run full test suite
6. Update `handoff.md`

## Rollback Point
- Git commit: `git stash` before starting
- If blocked: revert to `HEAD~1`

## Constraints
- Do NOT change the public API shape
- Do NOT use any external JWT library — use Node.js built-in `crypto`
